  <description><![CDATA[<p>Opatija and the Kvarner Riviera, once the stylish seaside retreat of the Austro-Hungarian aristocracy, are a unique combination of climate, culture and flora. In addition to the seaside promenade known as ‘Lungomare’, stretching over 12km, the slopes of Mount Ucka provide some breathtaking scenery for more energetic walkers. These slopes rise dramatically from the water’s edge and have an almost alpine character in contrast with the Mediterranean ambience of Opatija. Nearby Lovran is well worth a visit and you’ll find interesting traditional villages overlooking this most picturesque of coastlines. Enjoy the civilised ambience of Opatija holidays and its many diverse attractions.</p>]]></description>
