  <excursions><![CDATA[<p><strong>Pre-Bookable</strong>* </p>
<p><strong>Plitvice Lakes</strong> £46, full day, Tuesday<br />A perfect way to see one of the most stunning national parks of Croatia and includes a guided tour of the lakes, a moderate walk (approx 2 hrs), boat trip and visits to some amazing waterfalls.</p>
<p><strong>Uĉka National Park</strong> £33, full day, Monday<br />Get to know the history of the impressive Mount Ucka, stroll through the natural geological monuments of Vela Draga and enjoy breathtaking views from the highest Istrian mountain peak.</p>
<p><strong>Book Locally</strong> | Prices are shown for guidance only.</p>
<p><strong>Venice</strong> £70, by hydrofoil, full day, Tuesday &amp; Friday<br />A great opportunity to visit the most unique city in the world. Includes a sightseeing tour with a guide and free time to explore.</p>
<p><strong>Krk</strong> £35, full day<br />A chance to see one of the largest islands of the Kvarner Bay. Includes a visit to Košljun and the old town of Krk. There is an opportunity to taste the local wine with cured ham and cheeses.</p>
<p><strong>Two Islands Fish Picnic</strong> £32, full day<br />Cruise the islands of Cres and Krk stopping at pebble beaches to relax and sunbathe. The fish lunch is served on board along with music and singing with the captain. A fun day out.</p>
<p><strong>Hidden Istria</strong> £40, full day<br />Explore the hidden gems of the region such as the pirates’ nest Dvigrad, vampire’s village Kringa Motovun and the fort of Dragu which houses medieval frescoes.</p>
<p><strong>Istra Tour</strong> £37, full day<br />This full day tour takes you to some of the highlights of the area and visits historic Pula, Rovinj and Porec returning through the attractive scenery of central Istria.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>*Pre-bookable excursions do not run in May, however there will be a selection of </em><em>excursions available to book locally. Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions.</em></p>]]></excursions>
