  <walkingMap><![CDATA[<p>Opatija, situated at the foot of mighty Mt Ucka (1,400m) and its National Park, offers wonderful walking opportunities. There are a variety of marked trails through the national park with dotted waterfalls. The 12km Lungomare, between fishing village of Volosko to Lovran, offers an enjoyable walk with beautiful scenery. Many traditional mountain villages around Opatija offer wonderful views towards the Kvarner Bay.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Walking Tour of Opatija I Easy I 1½ hrs (approx) I</p>
<p><br />A guided city walk through the Angiolina Park, the historic centre and the Lungomare - a step back in time to the popular 19th century royal Austro-Hungarian health resort (Opatija) and its unique surroundings.</p>
<p><br />Carmen Sylva Promenade I Moderate I 3 hrs (approx) I 180m above sea level I</p>
<p><br />This guided walk takes you along a mostly shaded hillside path in the wooded area above Opatija and on to a local village and down on steps and slope to Volosko fishing village, return stroll on the Lungomare.</p>
<p>Please Note: walks are available on a first come first served basis and also subject to weather conditions. Please register with your rep on arrival.</p>]]></walkingMap>
